</section>

<section id="jgbox2" class="thematic-findings">
    <div class="container pt-5">
        <div class="row justify-content-center flex">
            <div class="col-md-11 mt-2">
                <p>
                    These four dimensions were operationalized through the Legal Needs Survey implemented in Italy as part of the <i>WJP EUROVOICES</i> project, which allows these measures to be statistically representative at the subnational level (using the Nomenclature of territorial units for statistics, or NUTS, at the NUTS1 level).
                </p>
                <h4 class="w-full font-medium text-[#575796]">
                    One Single Indicator: The Civil and Administrative Justice Gap
                </h4>
                <p>
                    To construct a single measure of unmet legal need, the four dimensions described above were averaged to produce a score for each respondent on a scale from 0 to 1. Individuals with an average score below 0.67—meaning that at least one-third of their basic justice needs were unmet—were classified as falling within the justice gap. In other words, when we state in this report that nearly half of people fall within the justice gap, it means that this share of the population did not receive one-third of the fundamental resources that every civil and administrative justice system should provide.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
